
[1]pavan

   PAVAN', n. [L. pavo, a peacock.] A grave dance among the Spaniards. In
   this dance, the performers make a kind of wheel before each other, the
   gentlemen dancing with cap and sword,princes with long robes, and the
   ladies with long trails; the motions resembling the stately steps of
   the peacock.
